ise if I have everything wrong, I am but 24 seasons so my &quot;end-game&quot; experiance is nil<br><br>CONGRATULATIONS to Fire and Fury on the killing of the first three warders!! Well Done!!<br><br>May I ask if Fire and Fury intend to awaken the sleeper??<br><br>I have heard this changes forever the server  including some quests, and also from a role-play standpoint, from what I can tell from their charter (nice website Baron Gore, liked it alot), bringing about an apocolyptic event isnt in it.  So are you stopping at three warders?  and will you give us warning if you plan on massacring the fourth in the same way as the other three?  (oh  and will those other three be reborn  or are they dead permanently?)<br><br>If I am wrong about all this please tell me to shut up hehe  Oh  and I'd rather no flames please, I deliberately posted this is a forum other than the soapbox.<br> <p><b>Elyta</b><Br><i>Gnome Illusionist</i><Br><i>Member of the </i><a href=http://www.tinkerspride.com>Tinker's Pride</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seeker of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 196<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 1:58:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Well not being from FnF I cannot tell you what they expect to do about the Sleeper.<br><br>However you are correct on some points... once all the Warders are killed the Sleeper awakes and start wasting everyone in the Tomb zone. To this day noone has ever survived this encounter.<br>Then he zones to other area of the game (Veeshan's Peak among others) and does the same to anyone there too. Then he despawns.<br><br>Once the Sleepers has been awaken, neither him nor the Warders are seen again.<br><br>Note that there are zone wide messages that appear when the Sleepers has awaken urging you to go hide in safer zones.<br><br>I'm still wondering to this day what will be the difference between the servers where he's been awaken and those where he hasn't when the final days of EQ will come.<br><br>Den <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubakanome.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bakanome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 94<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 2:04:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Well, basically, when the Sleeper awakens, quite a few, those who can, flood over to Velious for the sheer hell of being killed by the energy dragon.  I personally wouldn't mind if he came on a rampage around Antonica itself and the Faydwer.  I can't imagine the amount of shouts that would go on as a massive energy dragon runs through the Faydark hitting random d00ds for 1900 *grins* <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/udeneteth1.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Deneteth1</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Seeker of Truth</span><br>  Posts: 197<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 2:09:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://deneteth.freeservers.com/image/den2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Well if it was the case you would have a massive number of d00d between the four spires praying for the Nexus to become active before the Sleeper is done with the ones on orc hills...<br><br>That would make a very nice AE target <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 3:53:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> At the risk of making this into yet another FnF vs Reso flame war (or a debate on the merits of waking or not waking), I have begun to wonder if either of the high-end guilds (or the other ones quickly rising to that point) has any intent of waking the Sleeper. <br><br>I could care less if they do so to prevent someone else from doing it or as an accomplishment they can claim (&amp; it would be a heck of an accomplishment from what I have read).  Actually, even from merely a curiousity factor, it doesn't really matter to the life of my one way or the other if any of them are going to do it.  I am just and only curious as a player.<br><br>-Caillou<br>&lt;Grand New Adventure&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uellywig.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ellywig</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 314<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 3:58:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Sad that folks gotta post that much buffer text just to include FnF and Reso in the same post anymore, isn't it?<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Ellywig</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>Bemused Non-Factor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ujarkellraven.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JarkellRaven</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 485<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 3:59:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Well, there are certain items which cannot be obtained once the sleeper is awakened... such as a very nice monk robe, and the rogue/bard gnome mask.  For those of us that hope to enter the tomb some day, but for whom the possibility is a ways off, waking the sleeper is a real issue... Sleeper's Tomb is a fun zone, and after he's awakened it's gone forever.  So here's hoping they don't plan to screw up that zone... there's only a few servers with the zone in tact that are left, Test and Firiona Vie being two of those.   Those that have him still, other than here, have him because the high level guilds have pledged never to wake him.<br><br>Jarkell Ravensteel<br>Dawn Rising <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwitherweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 4:08:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> We did not attempt to awaken the Sleeper.  I think it would be kind of silly for the first time there.<br><br>As for the future.. you're just going to have to wait and see -)<br><br>Witherweaver<br>60 Wizard<br>Fire and Fury <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usimanmistrunner.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SimanMistrunner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 58<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 5:07:23 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Guilds have every right to go after the fourth warder and unleash Sleeper.  It is true that once the Sleeper is awoken, certain irreversible changes will occur.  If someone is mad about this, in my mind there is only one entity you can point your finger at. Verant.  That's right, the folks that intentionally designed it this way.  If Fire and Fury doesn't do it, some other guild (or combination of guilds) probably will.<br><br>Where does that leave the rest of us?  Hmmm....lets see.  In addition to the high-end mobs in Luclin and Kunark, that Planes of Power expansion will likely have the nicest drops seen yet.<br><br>Siman Mistrunner<br>Druid of 53 Seasons <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchysl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chysl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 5:54:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> I'll be blunt (at the risk of causing a flame war), please do not awaken the sleeper.<br><br>Now, for some background.  I come from a guild on another server that has done just that.  I helped make the decision to do it.  The warders do not come back, no new quests of any enjoyment are created (which we had hoped was the case when we chose to awaken him).  Every guild which has made the decision to awaken the sleeper has regretted it (with maybe 1 or 2 exceptions who had done all the farming they would ever need to do).<br><br>The Sleeper will visit a few zones, kill a few people in those zones, and produce about an hour's worth of fun for those involved.<br><br>The warders will never be back, others will never have the enjoyment of visiting Sleepers in its intended state.  So, for one hour of shits and grins, you deprive an entire server of hours of fun within Sleepers.  If you really want to be deathtouched, you can journey up into PoA and relive the old school Cazic Thule days.<br><br>The key agreement lies in a commitment not to kill the FIRST warder, once someone is capable of killing the FOURTH.  Simply killing one particular warder is not enough, all 4 must be dead at the same time.  In terms of rare / powerful items, the first warder drops very little of value (Trust me, you'll be swimming in primal after just a handful of warder clearings).  The three items most people want are the Monk Robe, Sceptres of Destruction, and Gnome Masks.  Eliminating these 3 items from the server (which you will do if you awaken the sleeper) does very little to improve your position on the server.<br><br>Out of curiosity, were the primal weapons tradable?<br><br>Chysl <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 143<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 6:13:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1>    I don't think it'd degenerate into a flame war unless people start taking the approach of &quot;Please don't kill the sleeper so that us RP guilds can, we level slower&quot;.<br><br>   I don't think there's much wrong with &quot;Please don't kill the sleeper because I wanna try for a gnome mask too someday&quot;.<br><br>   It's there in the game, so they have every right to kill it if they want, but I don't think there's anything particularly wrong about pleading that they not do so <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Syll <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uapepsadisticdream.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Apep Sadisticdream</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>~Making your dreams<br> my personal playground~<br>  Sadistic Mage Admin</span><br>  Posts: 446<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 6:30:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=11>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://noirdaila.homestead.com/files/Apep.gif width=70 heigth=175></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> I doubt there will be primnal weapons ever again or anything to such caliber..<br><br>Verant regretted putting them in game from day 1...<br>God forbid a weapon worth the risk vs reward factor...<br><br>Maybe Planes of Power will prove me wrong <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Apep Sadisticdream ~Leader of Ebon Storm~"The world left in my hands, there's no one left to hear you scream, no one left to see you bleed" "Come and be with me and live my twisted dream" </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwitherweaver.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Witherweaver</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 57<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 6:40:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Yes, Primal weapons are tradable.<br><br>If you want to go to Sleeper's, go right ahead (well, kill Zlandicar and go right ahead).<br><br>Sleeper's Tomb was not intended to remain in it's current state forever.  If that was so Verant never would have implemented the process of killing the Sleeper and not having him come back.  Verant has made specific posts about this, stating effectively that there are some things that only a certain number of people should experience.  I.e. when someone does something to change the world, the world should be changed and not reset the next day.<br><br>And the first warder dropped a nice mask for me, thanks.<br><br>And I don't understand the statement about position on the server.  What do you mean?<br><br>Witherweaver<br>60 Wizard<br>Fire and Fury<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvalquisssilverpalm.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valquiss Silverpalm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 208<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 6:57:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=13>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> I personally would hope and prefer that the guilds capable of doing so don't wake the Sleeper, but I don't pretend to have any control over it and I won't lose sleep over it.  And if anyone does do it I will quietly congradulate them and mumble about it only to myself later on.<br><br>Fact is, I am level 51 now and perhaps at the higher end of the game.  Higher being a very, very relative term.  All the same I'm not sure I will ever be at the point that it's even worth thinking about the Sleepers Tomb as a zone, so why worry?  And I'm a hell of a lot closer to it than a lot of the people expressing such concern.<br><br>Typical story, that people who aren't at the end game seem far more obsessed about it than people who are.<br><br>Valquiss <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uchysl.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Chysl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 7:18:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Personally, I've seen the sleeper be awakened, I've helped search through the zone for quests following the release.<br><br>I can 100% tell you first hand, the fun you will have by releasing the sleeper will be far, far less then the fun you will have making return trips to the zone.  The Fourth warder fight is a VERY unique encounter when done correctly, there is no other fight quite like it (I won't spoil it, although Kreugen already did if you want to go looking, but it requires some unique tactics and timing).<br><br>I'd also argue that the third warder is a lot of fun.  Laughing when some poor melee gets hit with his AE and knows his death is pending was always something I looked forward to.<br><br>Ideally, waking the sleeper would be the starting point to some other larger series of world-changing  events, but the fact is VI never finished the whole story.  So, once the sleeper is awakw, here is what you get...<br><br>The Master of the Guards, The Progenitor (sp?), and The Final Arbiter will all still spawn (5 days) and continue to drop primal weapons.  So, primals will never be fully eliminated.  You can now farm the zone for an EXTREMELY rare prismatic scale that can be quested into some other items far less desirable than what dropped in the first place.  You'll have to look them up, but they'll make you laugh, I promise.<br><br>Lastly, no guild lasts forever, and people retire from EQ.  When you make the decision to eliminate the warders, you no longer have a means to re-equip new people in your guild.  In addition, future encounters may require larger numbers of people to have certain items than you originally thought:<br><br>Example:  To kill the AoW requires some pretty nifty agro management, passing agro from one specific warrior with his def disc engaged to another.  Sceptres of Destruction (SoD's) are one of the highest taunting weapons available in the game.  Most guilds were comfortable when 2 or 3 of their warriors had them, so they would always have a solid, heavy taunting, main tank online.  However, when it came time to fight the AoW, they wished they had more.<br><br>I may type some more later, but I hate marathon posts, and this one just passed the 10 mile mark.<br><br>Chysl<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usyllestraefv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Syllestrae FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 146<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 7:21:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> And I don't understand the statement about position on the server. What do you mean?<br><br>Witherweaver<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>He means your reputation (and I know you knew that <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br><br>That being said, I'm level <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 51</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> now, and can almost <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> guarantee</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> that by the time I'd gained the skill, levels, playtime, and gear to be fighting in Sleeper's tomb, I'd already be playing the new games that have come out (Shadowbane, EQ2, Star Wars, whatever... whee <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), so it's really not an issue worth worrying about.  <br><br>It's not an easy feat to do, and more power to the guilds that can squish their real-life existence down small enough to <br>accomplish it <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>- Syll<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=folodar>Folodar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 8:12:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> One should probably not wake dragons as powerful as the Sleeper unless one is well-prepared to make a major effort on assaulting and destroying the critter. Not that it can be done without fitting the entire population of all the highest guilds into the zone, of course, but one should at least be willing to make a concentrated effort at it with whatever meager resources are yours to access.<br><br>Of course, I don't know anythign about dragons. I'm only a young monk. Your mileage will probably vary. <p><I>A lurker replies to YOU for 5 points of damage! <I></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 486<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 10:15:31 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> Personally I do want to wake the sleeper. Just not yet.<br><br>I want other folks to have a chance of getting primal gear. Folks in my guild and folks in other guilds should have a chance to see this neat monster.<br><br>But c'mon... its a cool story line and one of those &quot;once in a lifetime&quot; events. Well ok, once in a server life time anyways. Who wouldnt want to be part of that?<br><br>But worry not. I don't think anyone on this server is selfish enough to wake this sleeping dragon until other folks get a chance to see him.<br><br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/umheddik.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mheddik</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 166<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/15/02 11:49:16 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Sleepers Tomb</span><hr size=1> I am against waking the Sleeper. If he could be killed, or the story continued, I could see a point. But he is unkillable, and the story progresses no further. Asleep he is L99, has 99 million HP, and is untouchable by melee or magic. In fact, I couldn't target him, so they apparently made his sleeping form one of those untargetable mobs.<br><br>Now, awake, he can be hurt. However, he is the same level as Vulak (L77) and has more than 200 times the HP (still 99 million). If you had 1000 L60 wizards with dragonbane and they all successfully cast 50 (!) dragonbanes on him (if dragonbane even works on him), that might do it. Obviously, while theoretically possible to kill him, it is realistically impossible, even if everyone on the server were L60 and the game's mechanics would allow them all into the same zone without the zone crashing or 95% of everyone going LD.<br><br>So, there is no progression to the story, there is no better loot you get for having awakened him (quite the opposite), and waking him precludes anyone else from ever seeing him or the warders again, which seems to me to be a very selfish and anti-social thing to do. No, not everyone can or will be able to enter the Tomb, but for those who can, why deny them the sight of the Sleeper resting.<br><br>If he is awakened I won't shed any tears, but I will certainly think less of those who awaken him, for being selfish and viewing their ability to see a one-hour dead-end script as more important than everyone coming after them being able to see the Sleeper at all.<br><br>Coriolis, Sage of Erudin, Phantasmist, Firiona Vie<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukreelosthehunter.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kreelos the Hunter</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/16/02 12:04:01 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Making a claim that will never matter</span><hr size=1> I doubt I'll ever be high enough level to wake the Sleeper.  But if I ever could I would.<br><br>Why?<br><br>Because once, just ONCE I would like to see something happened that actually had a permanent impact on the world.  You can kill Kane Bayle 100 times and it won't stop the corruption in Qeynos.  You can wipe out every Gnoll in Blackburrow and they'll be back in an hour.  You can lead a raid on Neriak itself and kill the entire population and it won't stop Dark Elves from being created as PCs.  I'm not saying these things can or should be permanent changes but the one thing, the ONE thing that can change permanently I'd certainly do if no one beat me too it (and someone will, or I'll never be powerful enough to participate in changing it). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Giver of da juice (tm)</span><br>  Posts: 497<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(5/16/02 1:27:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1964.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Making a claim that will never matter</span><hr size=1> Cori is 100% right.<br><br>But I agree with the last poster too =)<br><br>Again, I hope the sleeper doesnt get woken up for a loooong time. But A little part of me hopes to at least be online and in one of the zones to see this beast rampage through the lands.<br><br>Verant regrets designing this encounter and has already made small changes to it. Apparently they have more changes in mind to make this zone &quot;more useful&quot;.<br><br>Who knows what the future will bring...<br> <p>Kzan Verto<BR>Giver of "da juice" (tm)<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=220314" target="new">My Magelo Profile</a></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1964.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1964.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1964.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1964.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showMessageRange?topicID=1964.topic&start=101&stop=115>6</a> </td><td align=right valign="top